I need to identify the financing costs incurred by the enterprise to raise funds needed for production and operation.

Looking at the income statement, the item that represents financing costs is typically labeled as "Financial Expenses" or similar terms. In this case, I can clearly see the line item "Financial Expenses" with a value of 67135.35 as of 2024-02-05.

Financial expenses generally include costs like interest expenses on loans, commitment fees, finance charges, etc. - all costs related to raising or borrowing funds for the business operations.

Therefore, the financing costs incurred by the enterprise is 67135.35.
